<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 12:59PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHWESTERN BEDFORD AND EAST
CENTRAL SOMERSET COUNTIES THROUGH 130 PM EDT...
At 1259 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Windber, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation possible.
Locations impacted include...
Central City, Indian Lake, Schellsburg, Manns Choice and New Paris.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
